  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Defective Verbs (الفعل الناقص)",
      "titleArabic": "الفعل الناقص",
      "content": [
        "Defective verbs (الفعل الناقص) have و or ي as their third (final) radical. This weak letter changes or drops in various conjugations.",
        "In the past tense, the final radical may appear as ا (alif) or ى (alif maqsūrah). In the present tense, it appears as و or ي."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Third radical is و or ي",
        "Past tense endings: ـَا (dawa), ـَى (ramā)",
        "دَعَا (to call/pray) - from root د-ع-و",
        "رَمَى (to throw) - from root ر-م-ي",
        "مَشَى (to walk) - from root م-ش-ي",
        "بَكَى (to cry) - from root ب-ك-ي"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "دَعَا رَبَّهُ", "english": "He called upon his Lord" },
        { "arabic": "رَمَى الْكُرَةَ", "english": "He threw the ball" },
        { "arabic": "مَشَى إِلَى الْمَدْرَسَةِ", "english": "He walked to school" },
        { "arabic": "بَكَى الطِّفْلُ", "english": "The child cried" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Present Tense of Defective Verbs",
      "titleArabic": "المضارع من الفعل الناقص",
      "content": [
        "In the present tense, defective verbs show their original final radical (و or ي), with changes in certain forms."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "دَعَا → يَدْعُو (he calls)",
        "رَمَى → يَرْمِي (he throws)",
        "مَشَى → يَمْشِي (he walks)",
        "In jussive, the final weak letter drops: لَمْ يَدْعُ، لَمْ يَرْمِ"
      ]
    }
  ],
